Reasoning: The paper proposes a deep recurrent neural network architecture based on the Sequence-2-Sequence model, which is a widely used model in natural language processing (NLP) and computer vision (CV) tasks. The proposed architecture is used to solve a non-polynomial (NP) hard problem, which falls under the category of artificial intelligence (AI). The use of recurrent networks and meta-heuristics algorithms suggests that the paper may also belong to the categories of machine learning (ML) and neural networks (NE). Finally, the smoothing of the loss function using homotopy continuation suggests that the paper may also belong to the category of computational linguistics (CL).
